{"metadata":{"title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","title":"MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"title":"overlayBounds","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBo